<subSubSection id="C7183E969D47B00C3D29E8B4C884ED8F" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="319CE1E5A4D980AE6022403B076D8563" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E4C14C02B423467E81E22E6362BC484" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="353A1EABB96EFB21892C6E1BDDB9D613" authorityName="Kang" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Retusigaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Retusigaster pulawskii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulawskii">
<emphasis id="35BD1458888E8DCAD917810642E6E87F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Retusigaster pulawskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="BF97A18510DE8925CDF91D9BEB981D43" class="Insecta" genus="R." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="R. albopilosus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albopilosus">
<emphasis id="25AF0D0458EEC393C4E0011048B0AB80" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">R. albopilosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The following characters can distinguish the new species from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="F4861293DEB01F9EA75DAB70ED684A1A" authorityName="Dangerfield, Austin &amp; Whitfield" authorityYear="1999" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Retusigaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Retusigaster" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CC6A6C21B984F080AF02C06F7255DFEE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Retusigaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: precoxal sulcus not reaching posterior margin of mesopleuron (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6158BCBD957D317E9D7BCA5468D54D1E" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Retusigaster pulawskii sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal propodeum to T 3 E wings F dorsal mesosoma G mesopleuron and metapleuron." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668119" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">2G</figureCitation>
); fore tibia entirely pale (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A8D8927D0F8B6DAD70D3E962E7DAA328" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Retusigaster pulawskii sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal propodeum to T 3 E wings F dorsal mesosoma G mesopleuron and metapleuron." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668119" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">2A</figureCitation>
); fore wing apically infuscate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6992F54CFCF842812403B708EF10B005" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Retusigaster pulawskii sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal propodeum to T 3 E wings F dorsal mesosoma G mesopleuron and metapleuron." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668119" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">2E</figureCitation>
); transverse carina of propodeum reaching lateral margin (Figs 
<figureCitation id="3B29F46543B4B42FDA159CFCCC3071C9" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Retusigaster pulawskii sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal propodeum to T 3 E wings F dorsal mesosoma G mesopleuron and metapleuron." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668119" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">2D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DB6203D7F0BE4617D2EE1182E640966F" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Retusigaster pulawskii sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal propodeum to T 3 E wings F dorsal mesosoma G mesopleuron and metapleuron." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668119" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">2F</figureCitation>
); stigma entirely dark (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2851CED93658380BCD71C89EDB79417E" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Retusigaster pulawskii sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal propodeum to T 3 E wings F dorsal mesosoma G mesopleuron and metapleuron." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668119" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">2E</figureCitation>
); hind femur entirely pale (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6DB903DD428B9F322144C2D23D7A4803" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Retusigaster pulawskii sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal propodeum to T 3 E wings F dorsal mesosoma G mesopleuron and metapleuron." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668119" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">2A</figureCitation>
); metasoma mostly dark (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="80CFAE11BCC8E27A451116469D2FA8F1" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Retusigaster pulawskii sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal propodeum to T 3 E wings F dorsal mesosoma G mesopleuron and metapleuron." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668119" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">2B</figureCitation>
); T1 laterally orange (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="92E0B444089D60E2775F57519B16EA5A" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Retusigaster pulawskii sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal propodeum to T 3 E wings F dorsal mesosoma G mesopleuron and metapleuron." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668119" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">2D</figureCitation>
); Y-shaped suture of T1entirely smooth (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="788E615E62E1CE28295455DDDBCAEE16" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Retusigaster pulawskii sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal propodeum to T 3 E wings F dorsal mesosoma G mesopleuron and metapleuron." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668119" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">2D</figureCitation>
); T2 medially orange (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="60A56EE18DCE20899C077D101403C2C7" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Retusigaster pulawskii sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal propodeum to T 3 E wings F dorsal mesosoma G mesopleuron and metapleuron." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668119" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">2D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="1B185106B8600AC0D95D3F8B9103C109" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668119" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
